This paper deals with the capacity of a Gaussian channel with one-bit quantization, which is a topic in information theory and communication theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of flash-signaling input distributions, which is related to signal processing and machine learning, making cs.SI (Signal Processing) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the Rayleigh-fading channel, which is a topic in networked systems and networked control, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of asymmetric signaling constellations, which is related to optimization and mathematical programming, making cs.MA (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
